<section xml:id="sec-plotting" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>plotting</title>
    <p>
        Let's examine the the vector <m>[-2, 3]</m>.
    </p>
    <sage>
        <input>
            vector([-2, 3])
        </input>
        <output>
            
        </output>
    </sage>
    <p>
         To plot the vector <m>[x, y]</m> The first number represents the x-coordinate, and the second number represents the y-coordinate.
    </p>
    <sage>
        <input>
            v = vector([-2, 3])
            plot(v)
        </input>
        <output>
            
        </output>
    </sage>
    <p>
        To plot a 3D vector, we can use the <c>plot3d</c> function. The first number represents the x-coordinate, the second number represents the y-coordinate, and the third number represents the z-coordinate.
    </p>
    <sage>
        <input>
            v = vector([1, 2, 3])
            arrow3d((0, 0, 0), v)
        </input>
        <output>
            
        </output>
    </sage>
    
</section>